      "span_text": "(60) Moreover, it has been reported that the supplementation of exogenous antioxidants (vitamins A and E) reduced 8-OHdG levels in dietary iron overloaded rats. [CITATION_1] These evidences in vivo and in vitro studies suggest that iron overload in the cytoplasm contributes, through the production of ROS, to both cellular damage and hepatocarcinogenesis.",
